Spotted a tiny thing. Not really important. Nice work on the guide btw :)

``` js
// good (slower)
$sidebar.find('ul');

// good (faster)
$($sidebar[0]).find('ul');
```

Not sure it's worth preferring such micro-optimizations, but FWIW the former is marginally faster.

In the [Type Casting & Coercion](https://github.com/airbnb/javascript#type-casting--coercion) section, you've got the following:

``` js
// bad
var val = inputValue >> 0;

// good
/**
 * parseInt was the reason my code was slow.
 * Bitshifting the String to coerce it to a
 * Number made it a lot faster.
 */
var val = inputValue >> 0;
```

